# Phase 8.4 — Content Agent Runtime Pipeline Rules

This rule applies only to Step 8.4 of Phase 8.

## Scope

Implement the Content Agent runtime pipeline.

## Rules

1. Implement `run_content_analysis()` or an equivalent pipeline entry point.
2. The pipeline must consume product context from validated input, coordinator-provided context, or Django client data according to existing project conventions.
3. Use the prompt template and brand voice behavior from Step 8.1.
4. Use `get_llm_provider()` / `MockProvider`; do not call provider SDKs directly.
5. Parse, normalize, apply Step 8.2 draft limits, and validate with Step 8.3 schemas before returning.
6. Handle empty or missing product data gracefully without hallucinating product facts.
7. Do not implement FastAPI `POST /run`; that belongs to Step 8.5.
8. Do not implement action persistence or Django `POST /internal/ai/actions/`; that belongs to Step 8.6.
9. Do not create `docs/examples/content_output.json`; that belongs to Step 8.7.
10. Do not add real Instagram publishing, external side effects, competitor scraping, website article generation, Support Agent logic, Coordinator/LangGraph orchestration, or frontend work.
11. Keep the implementation generic and multi-tenant. Do not hardcode Prestia-specific behavior.
12. Add focused deterministic tests using MockProvider or fixtures; no real LLM API keys.
13. Update `docs/phases/step-8.4.md` with implementation details, validation commands, and deferred work.
